&lt;p&gt;Keep in mind it’s OK to do nothing at all, too.&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 22 Feb 2021 04:49:26 -0600</pubDate></item><item><title>Dropbox-like (selective sync) OSS file synchronization for home</title><link>https://lobste.rs/s/vf3wez/dropbox_like_selective_sync_oss_file</link><description>&lt;p&gt;Hi, I really like how it is possible with Dropbox to have some files present locally and some only remotely.
Is there a similar open source solution? It could be a product but I would prefer an open source and something I can personally run at home.&lt;br&gt;
E.g I want to have my notes/keepass to be always present on my Android phone and desktop to allow offline access. The rest of the files could be remote only.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;My current solution is to have a SMB share and use Syncthing to sync a certain directory (e.g Notes). But combining multiple solutions feels a bit hacky so I am looking for alternatives.&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 23 Feb 2021 04:10:16 -0600</pubDate></item><item><title>Making our own executable packer</title><link>https://fasterthanli.me/series/making-our-own-executable-packer</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://lobste.rs/s/sizbxs/making_our_own_executable_packer"&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 23 Feb 2021 03:47:11 -0600</pubDate></item><item><title>Integrating Rust and C++ in Firefox</title><link>http://manishearth.github.io/blog/2021/02/22/integrating-rust-and-c-plus-plus-in-firefox/</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://lobste.rs/s/wcjdny/integrating_rust_c_firefox"&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 22 Feb 2021 16:56:04 -0600</pubDate></item><item><title>systemE: A lightweight systemd replacement written in Emacs lisp</title><link>https://github.com/grandfoobah/systemE</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://lobste.rs/s/gn5vbi/systeme_lightweight_systemd"&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 22 Feb 2021 19:39:20 -0600</pubDate></item><item><title>Mental Models Box</title><link>https://www.mentalmodelsbox.com/</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://lobste.rs/s/oq6nmf/mental_models_box"&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 23 Feb 2021 06:34:16 -0600</pubDate></item><item><title>Can we contain mutable data in imperative languages?</title><link>https://leontrolski.github.io/alter.html</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://lobste.rs/s/qstow5/can_we_contain_mutable_data_imperative"&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 22 Feb 2021 11:23:33 -0600</pubDate></item><item><title>Time for Next-Gen Codecs to Dethrone JPEG</title><link>https://cloudinary.com/blog/time_for_next_gen_codecs_to_det